data.meta_description: The actors will appear on the May 2 episode, 'Diss.'
data.text:
LAW & ORDER: SPECIAL VICTIMS UNIT Books Orlando Jones, Snoop Dogg, Amber Stevens West, and L. Scott Caldwell

LAW & ORDER: SPECIAL VICTIMS UNIT has set one heck of a guest cast for its May 2 episode, “Diss.”

In addition to Snoop Dogg appearing in the hour, the drama has also booked AMERICAN GODS’ Orlando Jones, GREEK’s Amber Stevens West, and LOST’s L. Scott Caldwell, NBC has confirmed.

The squad gets involved when a pop star (Stevens West) is attacked, and the very public feud between her rapper husband (Jones) and his rival (Snoop Dogg) gets brought into the case. (Fin also has a tie to a suspect, which puts him on the professional sidelines this episode.)

The long-running drama was recently renewed for its record-breaking 21st season (albeit down one series star).

Are you excited to see “Diss”?

LAW & ORDER: SPECIAL VICTIMS UNIT, Thursdays, 10/9c, NBC
